{"GOB":[{"def":"A little mass or collection; a small quantity; a mouthful.","pos":""}],"GOBANG":[{"def":"A Japanese game, played on a checkerboard, in which the object of the game is to be the first in placing five pieces, or men, in a row in any direction.","pos":""}],"GOBBET":[{"def":"A mouthful; a lump; a small piece.","pos":""}],"GOBBLE":[{"def":"To swallow or eat greedily or hastily; to gulp.","pos":""},{"def":"To utter (a sound) like a turkey cock.","pos":""}],"GOBBLER":[{"def":"A turkey cock; a bubbling Jock.","pos":""}],"GOBELIN":[{"def":"Pertaining to tapestry produced in the so-called Gobelin works, which have been maintained by the French Government since 1667.","pos":""}],"GOBEMOUCHE":[{"def":"Literally, a fly swallower; hence, once who keeps his mouth open; a boor; a silly and credulous person.","pos":""}],"GOBIOID":[{"def":"Like, or pertaining to, the goby, or the genus Gobius.","pos":""}],"GOBLET":[{"def":"A kind of cup or drinking vessel having a foot or standard, but without a handle.","pos":""}],"GOBLIN":[{"def":"An evil or mischievous spirit; a playful or malicious elf; a frightful phantom; a gnome.","pos":""}],"GOBLINE":[{"def":"One of the ropes or chains serving as stays for the dolphin striker or the bowsprit; -- called also gobrope and gaubline.","pos":""}],"GOBLINIZE":[{"def":"To transform into a goblin.","pos":""}],"GOBSTICK":[{"def":"A stick or device for removing the hook from a fish's gullet.","pos":""}],"GOBY":[{"def":"One of several species of small marine fishes of the genus Gobius and allied genera.","pos":""}]}